Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00

; Disable Fast Startup / Hibernation (default: 1)
; Fast Startup saves a hibernation image on shutdown and reloads it.
; Disabling this:
;   - Gives a true clean shutdown/boot (fixes many issues)
;   - Reduces SSD writes from hibernation file
;   - Fixes dual-boot issues
;   - May slightly increase boot time (2-5 seconds on SSD)

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\Power]
"HiberbootEnabled"=dword:00000000
